-- Turkey Central Bank to Narrow Rate Band Next Month, Sabah Says
-- B y   S i b e l   A k b a y
-- 2012-08-26T09:43:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-26/turkey-central-bank-to-narrow-rate-band-next-month-sabah-says.html
Turkey ’s central bank will begin to
narrow the upper end of the so-called interest-rate corridor
gradually starting next month,  Sabah  newspaper reported, citing
Governor Erdem Basci.  The central bank aims to proceed “cautiously,” Basci told
reporters in Ankara yesterday, the newspaper said. The  current-
account  gap will be between 7 percent and 8 percent of gross
domestic product by the end of the year, Sabah reported, citing
the banker.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sibel Akbay in Istanbul at 
